# RBAC, Security, Troubleshooting & CKA Prep

The final module: **lock it down** + **fix it** — what the CKA weighs most.

## Security

- **Identity** — Users (people, *not* objects) vs **ServiceAccounts** (Pods, real objects).
- **RBAC** — `Role`/`ClusterRole` bound by `RoleBinding`/`ClusterRoleBinding`. **Additive, no deny.** `auth can-i`.
- **Hardening** — **security context** (non-root, drop caps, read-only fs) · **PSA** per namespace · **etcd encryption** · supply chain.

## Troubleshooting (~30% of exam)

> Broken cluster → you fix it. Failure modes + first commands:
> **App** (`Pending`, `CrashLoop`) · **Control plane + node** (`NotReady`) · **Networking**.

## CKA strategy

> Time budget · aliases · `--dry-run=client -o yaml` · drill list.

> Frames the **RBAC + Security** boxes, then tours the **whole map**.
